THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 7 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. Except as otherwise provided in NRS 7.095 and 228.1116,
4 an attorney shall not contract for or collect a fee contingent on the
5 amount of recovery for representing a person seeking damages in
6 a civil action in excess of 20 percent of the amount recovered.
7 2. The limitation set forth in subsection 1 applies to all forms
8 of recovery, including, without limitation, settlement, arbitration
9 and judgment.
10 3. As used in this section, “recovered” means the net sum of
11 money recovered by the plaintiff after deducting any
12 disbursements or costs incurred in connection with the
13 prosecution or settlement of the claim.
14 Sec. 2. The amendatory provisions of this act apply to any
15 contract entered into on or after October 1, 2025.
